optimized_sql: WITH date_seq_cte AS (SELECT DISTINCT d_month_seq FROM date_dim WHERE d_year = 2002 AND d_moy = 3) SELECT a.ca_state AS state, COUNT(*) AS cnt FROM customer_address a, customer c, store_sales s, date_dim d, item i, date_seq_cte ds WHERE a.ca_address_sk = c.c_current_addr_sk AND c.c_customer_sk = s.ss_customer_sk AND s.ss_sold_date_sk = d.d_date_sk AND s.ss_item_sk = i.i_item_sk AND d.d_month_seq = ds.d_month_seq AND i.i_current_price > 1.2 * (SELECT AVG(j.i_current_price) FROM item j WHERE j.i_category = i.i_category) GROUP BY a.ca_state HAVING COUNT(*) >= 10 ORDER BY cnt, a.ca_state LIMIT 100
